In the court papers, Sonko said that at the rally, he did not make any utterances that amounted to incitement to commit violence.His lawyer John Khaminwa said that Sonko considers himself a whistleblower. The High Court has declined a request by former Nairobi Governor Mike Sonko to stop the Directorate of Criminal Investigation (DCI) from questioning him over remarks on poll chaos that were allegedly staged. 
Sonko wanted the court to grant an order against Assistant Inspector-General John Kariuki's decision to summon him to the DCI headquarters to record a statement.



