The senior police officer, who is also the Investigations Bureau director at the DCI  headquarters, had directed Sonko to appear for questioning on alleged offences of "undermining the authority of a public officer, incitement to violence and disobedience of the law".
He is expected to shed light on claims he made at a public rally - that together with Interior Principal Secretary Karanja Kibicho, they planned violence in Nairobi during the 2017 General Election.



